<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-968] SyslogLayout contains extra space</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-968</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a extra space in the SyslogLayout so that that message is not compliant with the BSD format:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    /**
     * Date format used &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; header = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;.
     */
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; SimpleDateFormat dateFormat = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; SimpleDateFormat(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;MMM dd HH:mm:ss &quot;&lt;/span&gt;, Locale.ENGLISH);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note the extra space at the end of the date format.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When this is used, another space is appended afterwards all the same:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        addDate(event.getTimeMillis(), buf);
        buf.append(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos; &apos;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This leads to incorrect data containing two spaces between the date field and the localHostname.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
